&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT BEZOS ACADEMY&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Bezos Academy, we believe all children deserve the great start that excellent early education provides, including in under-resourced communities. Our mission is to nurture the potential in every child to become a creative leader, original thinker, and lifelong learner by inventing the solutions needed to scale early childhood education. We are a unique organization that operates a multi-state network of schools offering quality Montessori preschool at no cost to families in under-resourced communities while also investing in creating tools, products, technology, and other solutions designed to reach children well beyond the walls of our schools. We aspire to have a profound, large-scale impact on children ages zero to five.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE POSITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Controller (internally titled Director, Accounting &amp;amp; Controller) at Bezos Academy, you will evaluate and manage effective accounting and reporting policies, procedures, and systems with a focus on using technology and data to drive continuous improvement. You will own all end-to-end accounting processes, including accounts payable, fixed assets, leasing, tax, treasury management, payroll operations, and the overall financial close process. You will oversee technical accounting research for US GAAP and tax-related matters and will prepare external tax and financial reports. You will own and refine policies and procedures to support a strong internal control environment. You will lead and develop a team to support these activities and the growth of our organization. Above all, you are a mission-driven, experienced accounting professional willing to roll up your sleeves and manage the accounting operation while iterating on the systems and processes necessary to scale our organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOCATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seattle, WA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role is expected to work in-person with other finance and partner team members in our office in the Eastlake neighborhood of Seattle at least two days a week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation support is available for those willing to relocate to Seattle, WA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPENSATION &amp;amp; BENEFITS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
