&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT BEZOS ACADEMY&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Bezos Academy, we believe all children deserve the great start that excellent early education provides, including in under-resourced communities. Our mission is to nurture the potential in every child to become a creative leader, original thinker, and lifelong learner by inventing the solutions needed to scale early childhood education. We are a unique organization that realizes our mission in two ways. First, we operate a multi-state network of schools in under-resourced communities, offering quality Montessori-inspired preschool at no cost to families. Second, we create tools, products, technology, and other solutions designed to reach young children and their caregivers well beyond the walls of our schools. We aspire to have a profound, large-scale impact on children ages zero to five.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;DESCRIPTION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior People Partner (HR Business Partner or HRBP) at Bezos Academy, you will serve as a trusted advisor to leaders, managers, and school staff nationwide, partnering across the organization to drive learning and development, organizational and workforce planning, performance management, goal setting, and other people processes. Using data, analytics, and strong relationships, you will translate people strategy into effective team execution, support employee relations and career growth, and help create an outstanding employee experience where teams are set up to thrive and deliver exceptional outcomes for children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You bring a broad spectrum of human resources experience from prior HR generalist and/or business partner roles or similar. Further, you demonstrate strong business acumen, a grounded and consultative approach, and the ability to build trusted relationships across lines of difference while helping a diverse national workforce navigate challenge and change.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
